        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:47PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Agate, or 15 miles west of Limon, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Hail may
accumulate on roadways causing hazardous travel.

Locations impacted include...
Agate.

This includes Interstate 70 between mile markers 341 and 350.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
